38template <class T>
39struct physical_bits {
40 static constexpr size_t value = sizeof(T) * std::numeric_limits<unsigned char>::digits;
41};

43struct value_bits {
44 static constexpr size_t value =

49// These classes expose encoding specs of IEEE-754-like floating-point formats.
50// Currently available formats are IEEE-754 binary32 & IEEE-754 binary64.
51
52struct ieee754_binary32 {
53 static constexpr int total_bits = 32;
54 static constexpr int significand_bits = 23;
55 static constexpr int exponent_bits = 8;
56 static constexpr int min_exponent = -126;
57 static constexpr int max_exponent = 127;
58 static constexpr int exponent_bias = -127;
59 static constexpr int decimal_significand_digits = 9;
60 static constexpr int decimal_exponent_digits = 2;
61};
62
63struct ieee754_binary64 {
64 static constexpr int total_bits = 64;
65 static constexpr int significand_bits = 52;
66 static constexpr int exponent_bits = 11;
67 static constexpr int min_exponent = -1022;
68 static constexpr int max_exponent = 1023;
69 static constexpr int exponent_bias = -1023;
70 static constexpr int decimal_significand_digits = 17;
71 static constexpr int decimal_exponent_digits = 3;
72};

74// A floating-point format traits class defines ways to interpret a bit pattern
75// of given size as an encoding of floating-point number. This is an
76// implementation of such a traits class, supporting ways to interpret IEEE-754
77// binary floating-point numbers.
78template <class Format, class CarrierUInt, class ExponentInt = int>
79struct ieee754_binary_traits {
80 // CarrierUInt needs to have enough size to hold the entire contents of
81 // floating-point numbers. The actual bits are assumed to be aligned to the
82 // LSB, and every other bits are assumed to be zeroed.
83 static_assert(detail::value_bits<CarrierUInt>::value >= Format::total_bits,
84 "wjr::dragonbox: insufficient number of bits");
85 static_assert(std::is_unsigned<CarrierUInt>::value);
86
87 // ExponentUInt needs to be large enough to hold (unsigned) exponent bits as
88 // well as the (signed) actual exponent.
89 // todo: static overflow guard against intermediate computations.
90 static_assert(detail::value_bits<ExponentInt>::value >= Format::exponent_bits + 1,
91 "wjr::dragonbox: insufficient number of bits");
92 static_assert(std::is_signed<ExponentInt>::value);
93
94 using format = Format;
95 using carrier_uint = CarrierUInt;
96 static constexpr int carrier_bits = int(detail::value_bits<carrier_uint>::value);
97 using exponent_int = ExponentInt;
98
99 // Extract exponent bits from a bit pattern.
100 // The result must be aligned to the LSB so that there is no additional zero
101 // paddings on the right. This function does not do bias adjustment.
102 static constexpr exponent_int extract_exponent_bits(carrier_uint u) noexcept {
103 return exponent_int((u >> format::significand_bits) &
104 ((exponent_int(1) << format::exponent_bits) - 1));
105 }
106
107 // Extract significand bits from a bit pattern.
108 // The result must be aligned to the LSB so that there is no additional zero
109 // paddings on the right. The result does not contain the implicit bit.
110 static constexpr carrier_uint extract_significand_bits(carrier_uint u) noexcept {
111 return carrier_uint(u & ((carrier_uint(1) << format::significand_bits) - 1u));
112 }
113
114 // Remove the exponent bits and extract significand bits together with the
115 // sign bit.
116 static constexpr carrier_uint remove_exponent_bits(carrier_uint u) noexcept {
117 return carrier_uint(
118 u & ~(((carrier_uint(1) << format::exponent_bits) - 1u) << format::significand_bits));
119 }
120
121 // Shift the obtained signed significand bits to the left by 1 to remove the
122 // sign bit.
123 static constexpr carrier_uint remove_sign_bit_and_shift(carrier_uint u) noexcept {
124 return carrier_uint((carrier_uint(u) << 1) &
125 ((((carrier_uint(1) << (Format::total_bits - 1)) - 1u) << 1) | 1u));
126 }
127
128 // Obtain the actual value of the binary exponent from the extracted
129 // exponent bits.
130 static constexpr exponent_int binary_exponent(exponent_int exponent_bits) noexcept {
131 return exponent_int(exponent_bits == 0 ? format::min_exponent
132 : exponent_bits + format::exponent_bias);
133 }
134
135 // Obtain the actual value of the binary significand from the extracted
136 // significand bits and exponent bits.
137 static constexpr carrier_uint binary_significand(carrier_uint significand_bits,
138 exponent_int exponent_bits) noexcept {
139 return carrier_uint(exponent_bits == 0 ? significand_bits
140 : (significand_bits |
141 (carrier_uint(1) << format::significand_bits)));
142 }
143
144 /* Various boolean observer functions */
145
146 static constexpr bool is_nonzero(carrier_uint u) noexcept {
147 return (u & ((carrier_uint(1) << (format::significand_bits + format::exponent_bits)) -
148 1u)) != 0;
149 }
150 static constexpr bool is_positive(carrier_uint u) noexcept {
151 return u < (carrier_uint(1) << (format::significand_bits + format::exponent_bits));
152 }
153 static constexpr bool is_negative(carrier_uint u) noexcept { return !is_positive(u); }
154 static constexpr bool is_finite(exponent_int exponent_bits) noexcept {
155 return exponent_bits != ((exponent_int(1) << format::exponent_bits) - 1);
156 }
157 static constexpr bool has_all_zero_significand_bits(carrier_uint u) noexcept {
158 return ((u << 1) & ((((carrier_uint(1) << (Format::total_bits - 1)) - 1u) << 1) | 1u)) == 0;
159 }
160 static constexpr bool has_even_significand_bits(carrier_uint u) noexcept { return u % 2 == 0; }
161};
162
163// Convert between bit patterns stored in carrier_uint and instances of an
164// actual floating-point type. Depending on format and carrier_uint, this
165// operation might not be possible for some specific bit patterns. However, the
166// contract is that u always denotes a valid bit pattern, so the functions here
167// are assumed to be noexcept. Users might specialize this class to change the
168// behavior for certain types. The default provided by the library is to treat
169// the given floating-point type Float as either IEEE-754 binary32 or IEEE-754
170// binary64, depending on the bitwise size of Float.
171template <class Float>
172struct default_float_bit_carrier_conversion_traits {
173 // Guards against types that have different internal representations than
174 // IEEE-754 binary32/64. I don't know if there is a truly reliable way of
175 // detecting IEEE-754 binary formats. I just did my best here. Note that in
176 // some cases numeric_limits<Float>::is_iec559 may report false even if the
177 // internal representation is IEEE-754 compatible. In such a case, the user
178 // can specialize this traits template and remove this static sanity check
179 // in order to make Dragonbox work for Float.
180 static_assert(std::numeric_limits<Float>::is_iec559 && std::numeric_limits<Float>::radix == 2 &&
181 (detail::physical_bits<Float>::value == 32 ||
182 detail::physical_bits<Float>::value == 64),
183 "wjr::dragonbox: Float may not be of IEEE-754 binary32/binary64");
184
185 // Specifies the unsigned integer type to hold bitwise value of Float.
186 using carrier_uint = typename std::conditional<detail::physical_bits<Float>::value == 32,
187 uint32_t, uint64_t>::type;
188
189 // Specifies the floating-point format.
190 using format = typename std::conditional<detail::physical_bits<Float>::value == 32,
191 ieee754_binary32, ieee754_binary64>::type;
192
193 // Converts the floating-point type into the bit-carrier unsigned integer
194 // type.
195 static WJR_CONSTEXPR20 carrier_uint float_to_carrier(Float x) noexcept {
196 return bit_cast<carrier_uint>(x);
197 }
198
199 // Converts the bit-carrier unsigned integer type into the floating-point
200 // type.
201 static WJR_CONSTEXPR20 Float carrier_to_float(carrier_uint x) noexcept {
202 return bit_cast<Float>(x);
203 }
204};

206// Convenient wrappers for floating-point traits classes.
207// In order to reduce the argument passing overhead, these classes should be as
208// simple as possible (e.g., no inheritance, no private non-static data member,
209// etc.; this is an unfortunate fact about common ABI convention).
210
211template <class FormatTraits>
212struct signed_significand_bits {
213 using format_traits = FormatTraits;
214 using carrier_uint = typename format_traits::carrier_uint;
215
216 carrier_uint u;
217
218 signed_significand_bits() = default;
219 constexpr explicit signed_significand_bits(carrier_uint bit_pattern) noexcept
220 : u{bit_pattern} {}
221
222 // Shift the obtained signed significand bits to the left by 1 to remove the
223 // sign bit.
224 constexpr carrier_uint remove_sign_bit_and_shift() const noexcept {
225 return format_traits::remove_sign_bit_and_shift(u);
226 }
227
228 constexpr bool is_positive() const noexcept { return format_traits::is_positive(u); }
229 constexpr bool is_negative() const noexcept { return format_traits::is_negative(u); }
230 constexpr bool has_all_zero_significand_bits() const noexcept {
231 return format_traits::has_all_zero_significand_bits(u);
232 }
233 constexpr bool has_even_significand_bits() const noexcept {
234 return format_traits::has_even_significand_bits(u);
235 }
236};
237
238template <class FormatTraits>
239struct float_bits {
240 using format_traits = FormatTraits;
241 using carrier_uint = typename format_traits::carrier_uint;
242 using exponent_int = typename format_traits::exponent_int;
243
244 carrier_uint u;
245
246 float_bits() = default;
247 constexpr explicit float_bits(carrier_uint bit_pattern) noexcept : u{bit_pattern} {}
248
249 // Extract exponent bits from a bit pattern.
250 // The result must be aligned to the LSB so that there is no additional zero
251 // paddings on the right. This function does not do bias adjustment.
252 constexpr exponent_int extract_exponent_bits() const noexcept {
253 return format_traits::extract_exponent_bits(u);
254 }
255
256 // Extract significand bits from a bit pattern.
257 // The result must be aligned to the LSB so that there is no additional zero
258 // paddings on the right. The result does not contain the implicit bit.
259 constexpr carrier_uint extract_significand_bits() const noexcept {
260 return format_traits::extract_significand_bits(u);
261 }
262
263 // Remove the exponent bits and extract significand bits together with the
264 // sign bit.
265 constexpr signed_significand_bits<format_traits> remove_exponent_bits() const noexcept {
266 return signed_significand_bits<format_traits>(format_traits::remove_exponent_bits(u));
267 }
268
269 // Obtain the actual value of the binary exponent from the extracted
270 // exponent bits.
271 static constexpr exponent_int binary_exponent(exponent_int exponent_bits) noexcept {
272 return format_traits::binary_exponent(exponent_bits);
273 }
274 constexpr exponent_int binary_exponent() const noexcept {
275 return binary_exponent(extract_exponent_bits());
276 }
277
278 // Obtain the actual value of the binary exponent from the extracted
279 // significand bits and exponent bits.
280 static constexpr carrier_uint binary_significand(carrier_uint significand_bits,
281 exponent_int exponent_bits) noexcept {
282 return format_traits::binary_significand(significand_bits, exponent_bits);
283 }
284 constexpr carrier_uint binary_significand() const noexcept {
285 return binary_significand(extract_significand_bits(), extract_exponent_bits());
286 }
287
288 constexpr bool is_nonzero() const noexcept { return format_traits::is_nonzero(u); }
289 constexpr bool is_positive() const noexcept { return format_traits::is_positive(u); }
290 constexpr bool is_negative() const noexcept { return format_traits::is_negative(u); }
291 constexpr bool is_finite(exponent_int exponent_bits) const noexcept {
292 return format_traits::is_finite(exponent_bits);
293 }
294 constexpr bool is_finite() const noexcept {
295 return format_traits::is_finite(extract_exponent_bits());
296 }
297 constexpr bool has_even_significand_bits() const noexcept {
298 return format_traits::has_even_significand_bits(u);
299 }
300};
301
302template <class Float, class ConversionTraits = default_float_bit_carrier_conversion_traits<Float>,
303 class FormatTraits = ieee754_binary_traits<typename ConversionTraits::format,
304 typename ConversionTraits::carrier_uint>>
305WJR_CONSTEXPR20 float_bits<FormatTraits> make_float_bits(Float x) noexcept {
306 return float_bits<FormatTraits>(ConversionTraits::float_to_carrier(x));
307}

314namespace wuint {

316inline constexpr uint64_t umul64(uint32_t x, uint32_t y) noexcept {
317 return x * static_cast<uint64_t>(y);
318}
319
320// Get 128-bit result of multiplication of two 64-bit unsigned integers.
321WJR_SAFEBUFFERS WJR_INTRINSIC_CONSTEXPR20 uint128_t umul128(uint64_t x, uint64_t y) noexcept {
322 return mul64x64to128(x, y);
323}
324
325// Get high half of the 128-bit result of multiplication of two 64-bit unsigned
326// integers.
327WJR_SAFEBUFFERS WJR_INTRINSIC_CONSTEXPR20 uint64_t umul128_upper64(uint64_t x,
328 uint64_t y) noexcept {
329 return mulhi(x, y);
330}
331
332// Get upper 128-bits of multiplication of a 64-bit unsigned integer and a
333// 128-bit unsigned integer.
334WJR_SAFEBUFFERS WJR_INTRINSIC_CONSTEXPR20 uint128_t umul192_upper128(uint64_t x,
335 uint128_t y) noexcept {
336 auto r = umul128(x, y.high);
337 r += umul128_upper64(x, y.low);
338 return r;
339}
340
341// Get upper 64-bits of multiplication of a 32-bit unsigned integer and a 64-bit
342// unsigned integer.
343WJR_INTRINSIC_CONSTEXPR20 uint64_t umul96_upper64(uint32_t x, uint64_t y) noexcept {
344 return umul128_upper64(uint64_t(x) << 32, y);
345}
346
347// Get lower 128-bits of multiplication of a 64-bit unsigned integer and a
348// 128-bit unsigned integer.
349WJR_SAFEBUFFERS WJR_INTRINSIC_CONSTEXPR20 uint128_t umul192_lower128(uint64_t x,
350 uint128_t y) noexcept {
351 auto const high = x * y.high;
352 auto const high_low = umul128(x, y.low);
353 return {(high + high_low.high) & UINT64_C(0xffffffffffffffff), high_low.low};
354}
355
356// Get lower 64-bits of multiplication of a 32-bit unsigned integer and a 64-bit
357// unsigned integer.
358constexpr uint64_t umul96_lower64(uint32_t x, uint64_t y) noexcept {
359 return (x * y) & UINT64_C(0xffffffffffffffff);
360}
361} // namespace wuint

367template <int k, class Int>
368constexpr Int compute_power(Int a) noexcept {
369 static_assert(k >= 0);
370 Int p = 1;
371 for (int i = 0; i < k; ++i) {
372 p *= a;
373 }
374 return p;
375}
376
377template <int a, class UInt>
378constexpr int count_factors(UInt n) noexcept {
379 static_assert(a > 1);
380 int c = 0;
381 while (n % a == 0) {
382 n /= a;
383 ++c;
384 }
385 return c;
386}

389// Utilities for fast/constexpr log computation.

392namespace log {
393static_assert((std::int_fast32_t(-1) >> 1) == std::int_fast32_t(-1) &&
394 (std::int_fast16_t(-1) >> 1) == std::int_fast16_t(-1),
395 "wjr::dragonbox: right-shift for signed integers must be arithmetic");
396
397// For constexpr computation.
398// Returns -1 when n = 0.
399template <class UInt>
400constexpr int floor_log2(UInt n) noexcept {
401 int count = -1;
402 while (n != 0) {
403 ++count;
404 n >>= 1;
405 }
406 return count;
407}

409template <template <size_t> class Info, std::int32_t min_exponent, std::int32_t max_exponent,
410 size_t current_tier,
411 std::int32_t supported_min_exponent = Info<current_tier>::min_exponent,
412 std::int32_t supported_max_exponent = Info<current_tier>::max_exponent>
413constexpr bool is_in_range(int) noexcept {
414 return min_exponent >= supported_min_exponent && max_exponent <= supported_max_exponent;
415}
416
417template <template <size_t> class Info, std::int32_t min_exponent, std::int32_t max_exponent,
418 size_t current_tier>
419constexpr bool is_in_range(...) noexcept {
420 // Supposed to be always false, but formally dependent on the template
421 // parameters.
422 static_assert(min_exponent > max_exponent, "wjr::dragonbox: exponent range is too wide");
423 return false;
424}
425
426template <template <size_t> class Info, std::int32_t min_exponent, std::int32_t max_exponent,
427 size_t current_tier = 0,
428 bool = is_in_range<Info, min_exponent, max_exponent, current_tier>(0)>
429struct compute_impl;
430
431template <template <size_t> class Info, std::int32_t min_exponent, std::int32_t max_exponent,
432 size_t current_tier>
433struct compute_impl<Info, min_exponent, max_exponent, current_tier, true> {
434 using info = Info<current_tier>;
435 using default_return_type = typename info::default_return_type;
436 template <class ReturnType, class Int>
437 static constexpr ReturnType compute(Int e) noexcept {
438 WJR_ASSERT(min_exponent <= e && e <= max_exponent);
439 // The sign is irrelevant for the mathematical validity of the formula,
440 // but assuming positivity makes the overflow analysis simpler.
441 static_assert(info::multiply >= 0 && info::subtract >= 0);
442 return static_cast<ReturnType>((e * info::multiply - info::subtract) >> info::shift);
443 }
444};
445
446template <template <size_t> class Info, std::int32_t min_exponent, std::int32_t max_exponent,
447 size_t current_tier>
448struct compute_impl<Info, min_exponent, max_exponent, current_tier, false> {
449 using next_tier = compute_impl<Info, min_exponent, max_exponent, current_tier + 1>;
450 using default_return_type = typename next_tier::default_return_type;
451 template <class ReturnType, class Int>
452 static constexpr ReturnType compute(Int e) noexcept {
453 return next_tier::template compute<ReturnType>(e);
454 }
455};

622// Utilities for fast divisibility tests.
624
625namespace div {
626// Replace n by floor(n / 10^N).
627// Returns true if and only if n is divisible by 10^N.
628// Precondition: n <= 10^(N+1)
629// !!It takes an in-out parameter!!
630template <int N, class UInt>
631struct divide_by_pow10_info;
632
633template <class UInt>
634struct divide_by_pow10_info<1, UInt> {
635 static constexpr std::uint_fast32_t magic_number = 6554;
636 static constexpr int shift_amount = 16;
637};
638
639template <>
640struct divide_by_pow10_info<1, std::uint8_t> {
641 static constexpr std::uint_fast16_t magic_number = 103;
642 static constexpr int shift_amount = 10;
643};
644
645template <>
646struct divide_by_pow10_info<1, std::uint16_t> {
647 static constexpr std::uint_fast16_t magic_number = 103;
648 static constexpr int shift_amount = 10;
649};
650
651template <class UInt>
652struct divide_by_pow10_info<2, UInt> {
653 static constexpr std::uint_fast32_t magic_number = 656;
654 static constexpr int shift_amount = 16;
655};
656
657template <>
658struct divide_by_pow10_info<2, std::uint16_t> {
659 static constexpr std::uint_fast32_t magic_number = 41;
660 static constexpr int shift_amount = 12;
661};
662
663template <int N, class UInt>
664constexpr bool check_divisibility_and_divide_by_pow10(UInt &n) noexcept {
665 // Make sure the computation for max_n does not overflow.
666 static_assert(N + 1 <= log::floor_log10_pow2(int(value_bits<UInt>::value)));
667 WJR_ASSERT(n <= compute_power<N + 1>(UInt(10)));
668
669 using info = divide_by_pow10_info<N, UInt>;
670 using intermediate_type = decltype(info::magic_number);
671 auto const prod = intermediate_type(n * info::magic_number);
672
673 constexpr auto mask = intermediate_type((intermediate_type(1) << info::shift_amount) - 1);
674 bool const result = ((prod & mask) < info::magic_number);
675
676 n = UInt(prod >> info::shift_amount);
677 return result;
678}
679
680// Compute floor(n / 10^N) for small n and N.
681// Precondition: n <= 10^(N+1)
682template <int N, class UInt>
683constexpr UInt small_division_by_pow10(UInt n) noexcept {
684 // Make sure the computation for max_n does not overflow.
685 static_assert(N + 1 <= log::floor_log10_pow2(int(value_bits<UInt>::value)));
686 WJR_ASSERT(n <= compute_power<N + 1>(UInt(10)));
687
688 return UInt((n * divide_by_pow10_info<N, UInt>::magic_number) >>
689 divide_by_pow10_info<N, UInt>::shift_amount);
690}
691
692// Compute floor(n / 10^N) for small N.
693// Precondition: n <= n_max
694template <int N, class UInt, UInt n_max>
695WJR_INTRINSIC_CONSTEXPR20 UInt divide_by_pow10(UInt n) noexcept {
696 static_assert(N >= 0);
697
698 // Specialize for 32-bit division by 10.
699 // Without the bound on n_max (which compilers these days never leverage),
700 // the minimum needed amount of shift is larger than 32. Hence, this may
701 // generate better code for 32-bit or smaller architectures. Even for 64-bit
702 // architectures, it seems compilers tend to generate mov + mul instead of a
703 // single imul for an unknown reason if we just write n / 10.
704 if constexpr (std::is_same<UInt, uint32_t>::value && N == 1 && n_max <= UINT32_C(1073741828)) {
705 return UInt(wuint::umul64(n, UINT32_C(429496730)) >> 32);
706 }
707 // Specialize for 64-bit division by 10.
708 // Without the bound on n_max (which compilers these days never leverage),
709 // the minimum needed amount of shift is larger than 64.
710 else if constexpr (std::is_same<UInt, uint64_t>::value && N == 1 &&
711 n_max <= UINT64_C(4611686018427387908)) {
712 return UInt(wuint::umul128_upper64(n, UINT64_C(1844674407370955162)));
713 }
714 // Specialize for 32-bit division by 100.
715 // It seems compilers tend to generate mov + mul instead of a single imul
716 // for an unknown reason if we just write n / 100.
717 else if constexpr (std::is_same<UInt, uint32_t>::value && N == 2) {
718 return UInt(wuint::umul64(n, UINT32_C(1374389535)) >> 37);
719 }
720 // Specialize for 64-bit division by 1000.
721 // Without the bound on n_max (which compilers these days never leverage),
722 // the smallest magic number for this computation does not fit into 64-bits.
723 else if constexpr (std::is_same<UInt, uint64_t>::value && N == 3 &&
724 n_max <= UINT64_C(15534100272597517998)) {
725 return UInt(wuint::umul128_upper64(n, UINT64_C(4722366482869645214)) >> 8);
726 } else {
727 constexpr auto divisor = compute_power<N>(UInt(10));
728 return n / divisor;
729 }
730}
731} // namespace div
732} // namespace detail

1485// Compressed cache.
1486template <class FloatFormat, class Dummy = void>
1487struct compressed_cache_holder {
1488 using cache_entry_type = typename cache_holder<FloatFormat>::cache_entry_type;
1489 static constexpr int cache_bits = cache_holder<FloatFormat>::cache_bits;
1490 static constexpr int min_k = cache_holder<FloatFormat>::min_k;
1491 static constexpr int max_k = cache_holder<FloatFormat>::max_k;
1492
1493 template <class ShiftAmountType, class DecimalExponentType>
1494 static constexpr cache_entry_type get_cache(DecimalExponentType k) noexcept {
1495 return cache_holder<FloatFormat>::cache[k - min_k];
1496 }
1497};
1498
1499template <class Dummy>
1500struct compressed_cache_holder<ieee754_binary32, Dummy> {
1501 using cache_entry_type = cache_holder<ieee754_binary32>::cache_entry_type;
1502 static constexpr int cache_bits = cache_holder<ieee754_binary32>::cache_bits;
1503 static constexpr int min_k = cache_holder<ieee754_binary32>::min_k;
1504 static constexpr int max_k = cache_holder<ieee754_binary32>::max_k;
1505 static constexpr int compression_ratio = 13;
1506 static constexpr size_t compressed_table_size =
1507 size_t((max_k - min_k + compression_ratio) / compression_ratio);
1508 static constexpr size_t pow5_table_size = size_t((compression_ratio + 1) / 2);
1509
1510 using cache_holder_t = std::array<cache_entry_type, compressed_table_size>;
1511 using pow5_holder_t = std::array<std::uint16_t, pow5_table_size>;
1512
1513 static constexpr cache_holder_t cache WJR_STATIC_DATA_SECTION = [] {
1514 cache_holder_t res{};
1515 for (size_t i = 0; i < compressed_table_size; ++i) {
1516 res[i] = cache_holder<ieee754_binary32>::cache[i * compression_ratio];
1517 }
1518 return res;
1519 }();
1520 static constexpr pow5_holder_t pow5_table WJR_STATIC_DATA_SECTION = [] {
1521 pow5_holder_t res{};
1522 std::uint16_t p = 1;
1523 for (size_t i = 0; i < pow5_table_size; ++i) {
1524 res[i] = p;
1525 p *= 5;
1526 }
1527 return res;
1528 }();
1529
1530 template <class ShiftAmountType, class DecimalExponentType>
1531 static WJR_CONSTEXPR20 cache_entry_type get_cache(DecimalExponentType k) noexcept {
1532 // Compute the base index.
1533 // Supposed to compute (k - min_k) / compression_ratio.
1534 static_assert(max_k - min_k <= 89 && compression_ratio == 13);
1535 static_assert(max_k - min_k <= std::numeric_limits<DecimalExponentType>::max(), "");
1536 auto const cache_index = DecimalExponentType(
1537 std::uint_fast16_t(DecimalExponentType(k - min_k) * std::int_fast16_t(79)) >> 10);
1538 auto const kb = DecimalExponentType(cache_index * compression_ratio + min_k);
1539 auto const offset = DecimalExponentType(k - kb);
1540
1541 // Get the base cache.
1542 auto const base_cache = cache[cache_index];
1543
1544 if (offset == 0) {
1545 return base_cache;
1546 } else {
1547 // Compute the required amount of bit-shift.
1548 auto const alpha =
1549 ShiftAmountType(detail::log::floor_log2_pow10<min_k, max_k>(k) -
1550 detail::log::floor_log2_pow10<min_k, max_k>(kb) - offset);
1551 WJR_ASSERT(alpha > 0 && alpha < 64);
1552
1553 // Try to recover the real cache.
1554 auto const pow5 =
1555 offset >= 7
1556 ? std::uint_fast32_t(std::uint_fast32_t(pow5_table[6]) * pow5_table[offset - 6])
1557 : std::uint_fast32_t(pow5_table[offset]);
1558 const auto mul_result = detail::wuint::umul128(base_cache, pow5);
1559 auto const recovered_cache = cache_entry_type(
1560 (((mul_result.high << ShiftAmountType(64 - alpha)) | (mul_result.low >> alpha)) +
1561 1) &
1562 UINT64_C(0xffffffffffffffff));
1563 WJR_ASSERT(recovered_cache != 0);
1564
1565 return recovered_cache;
1566 }
1567 }
1568};
1569
1570template <class Dummy>
1571struct compressed_cache_holder<ieee754_binary64, Dummy> {
1572 using cache_entry_type = cache_holder<ieee754_binary64>::cache_entry_type;
1573 static constexpr int cache_bits = cache_holder<ieee754_binary64>::cache_bits;
1574 static constexpr int min_k = cache_holder<ieee754_binary64>::min_k;
1575 static constexpr int max_k = cache_holder<ieee754_binary64>::max_k;
1576 static constexpr int compression_ratio = 27;
1577 static constexpr size_t compressed_table_size =
1578 size_t((max_k - min_k + compression_ratio) / compression_ratio);
1579 static constexpr size_t pow5_table_size = size_t(compression_ratio);
1580
1581 using cache_holder_t = std::array<cache_entry_type, compressed_table_size>;
1582 using pow5_holder_t = std::array<uint64_t, pow5_table_size>;
1583
1584 static constexpr cache_holder_t cache WJR_STATIC_DATA_SECTION = [] {
1585 cache_holder_t res{};
1586 for (size_t i = 0; i < compressed_table_size; ++i) {
1587 res[i] = cache_holder<ieee754_binary64>::cache[i * compression_ratio];
1588 }
1589 return res;
1590 }();
1591 static constexpr pow5_holder_t pow5_table WJR_STATIC_DATA_SECTION = [] {
1592 pow5_holder_t res{};
1593 uint64_t p = 1;
1594 for (size_t i = 0; i < pow5_table_size; ++i) {
1595 res[i] = p;
1596 p *= 5;
1597 }
1598 return res;
1599 }();
1600
1601 template <class ShiftAmountType, class DecimalExponentType>
1602 static WJR_CONSTEXPR20 cache_entry_type get_cache(DecimalExponentType k) noexcept {
1603 // Compute the base index.
1604 // Supposed to compute (k - min_k) / compression_ratio.
1605 static_assert(max_k - min_k <= 619 && compression_ratio == 27);
1606 static_assert(max_k - min_k <= std::numeric_limits<DecimalExponentType>::max(), "");
1607 auto const cache_index = DecimalExponentType(
1608 std::uint_fast32_t(DecimalExponentType(k - min_k) * std::int_fast32_t(607)) >> 14);
1609 auto const kb = DecimalExponentType(cache_index * compression_ratio + min_k);
1610 auto const offset = DecimalExponentType(k - kb);
1611
1612 // Get the base cache.
1613 auto const base_cache = cache[cache_index];
1614
1615 if (offset == 0) {
1616 return base_cache;
1617 } else {
1618 // Compute the required amount of bit-shift.
1619 auto const alpha =
1620 ShiftAmountType(detail::log::floor_log2_pow10<min_k, max_k>(k) -
1621 detail::log::floor_log2_pow10<min_k, max_k>(kb) - offset);
1622 WJR_ASSERT(alpha > 0 && alpha < 64);
1623
1624 // Try to recover the real cache.
1625 auto const pow5 = pow5_table[offset];
1626 auto recovered_cache = detail::wuint::umul128(base_cache.high, pow5);
1627 auto const middle_low = detail::wuint::umul128(base_cache.low, pow5);
1628
1629 recovered_cache += middle_low.high;
1630
1631 auto const high_to_middle =
1632 uint64_t((recovered_cache.high << ShiftAmountType(64 - alpha)) &
1633 UINT64_C(0xffffffffffffffff));
1634 auto const middle_to_low =
1635 uint64_t((recovered_cache.low << ShiftAmountType(64 - alpha)) &
1636 UINT64_C(0xffffffffffffffff));
1637
1638 recovered_cache = {(recovered_cache.low >> alpha) | high_to_middle,
1639 ((middle_low.low >> alpha) | middle_to_low)};
1640
1641 WJR_ASSERT(recovered_cache.low != UINT64_C(0xffffffffffffffff));
1642 recovered_cache = {recovered_cache.high, uint64_t(recovered_cache.low + 1)};
1643
1644 return recovered_cache;
1645 }
1646 }
1647};

1821struct symmetric_boundary {

1825 constexpr bool include_right_endpoint() const noexcept { return is_closed; }

1827struct asymmetric_boundary {
1828 static constexpr bool is_symmetric = false;
1829 bool is_left_closed;

1831 constexpr bool include_right_endpoint() const noexcept { return !is_left_closed; }
1832};

1836 static constexpr bool include_right_endpoint() noexcept { return true; }

1839 static constexpr bool is_symmetric = true;
1840 static constexpr bool include_left_endpoint() noexcept { return false; }
1841 static constexpr bool include_right_endpoint() noexcept { return false; }

2161

2164 return significand % 2 != 0;
2165 }

2262inline constexpr struct minimal_t {

2265 template <class FormatTraits, uint64_t upper_bound>
2266 using remainder_type = typename std::conditional<
2267 upper_bound <= std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max(), std::uint8_t,
2268 typename std::conditional<
2269 upper_bound <= std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max(), std::uint16_t,
2270 typename std::conditional<
2271 upper_bound <= std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max(), uint32_t,

2273 uint64_t, typename FormatTraits::carrier_uint>::type>::
2274 type>::type>::type;
2275
2276 template <class FormatTraits, std::int32_t lower_bound, uint32_t upper_bound>
2277 using decimal_exponent_type = typename std::conditional<
2278 lower_bound >= std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::min() &&
2279 upper_bound <= std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max(),
2280 std::int8_t,
2281 typename std::conditional<
2282 lower_bound >= std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::min() &&
2283 upper_bound <= std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max(),
2284 std::int16_t,
2285 typename std::conditional<lower_bound >= std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min() &&
2286 upper_bound <= std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max(),
2287 std::int32_t,
2288 typename FormatTraits::exponent_int>::type>::type>::type;
2289
2290 template <class FormatTraits>
2291 using shift_amount_type = std::int8_t;
2292} minimal;
2293} // namespace preferred_integer_types
2294} // namespace policy
2295
2297// Specializations of user-specializable templates used in the main algorithm.
2299
2300template <class DecimalExponentType>
2301struct remove_trailing_zeros_traits<policy::trailing_zero::remove_t, ieee754_binary32, uint32_t,
2302 DecimalExponentType> {
2303 WJR_INTRINSIC_INLINE static constexpr void
2304 remove_trailing_zeros(uint32_t &significand, DecimalExponentType &exponent) noexcept {
2305 // See https://github.com/jk-jeon/rtz_benchmark.
2306 // The idea of branchless search below is by reddit users r/pigeon768
2307 // and r/TheoreticalDumbass.
2308
2309 auto r = rotr(uint32_t(significand * UINT32_C(184254097)), 4);
2310 auto b = r < UINT32_C(429497);
2311 auto s = size_t(b);
2312 significand = b ? r : significand;
2313
2314 r = rotr(uint32_t(significand * UINT32_C(42949673)), 2);
2315 b = r < UINT32_C(42949673);
2316 s = s * 2 + b;
2317 significand = b ? r : significand;
2318
2319 r = rotr(uint32_t(significand * UINT32_C(1288490189)), 1);
2320 b = r < UINT32_C(429496730);
2321 s = s * 2 + b;
2322 significand = b ? r : significand;
2323
2324 exponent += s;
2325 }
2326};

2328template <class DecimalExponentType>
2329struct remove_trailing_zeros_traits<policy::trailing_zero::remove_t, ieee754_binary64, uint64_t,
2330 DecimalExponentType> {
2331 WJR_INTRINSIC_INLINE static constexpr void
2332 remove_trailing_zeros(uint64_t &significand, DecimalExponentType &exponent) noexcept {
2333 // See https://github.com/jk-jeon/rtz_benchmark.
2334 // The idea of branchless search below is by reddit users r/pigeon768
2335 // and r/TheoreticalDumbass.
2336
2337 auto r = rotr(uint64_t(significand * UINT64_C(28999941890838049)), 8);
2338 auto b = r < UINT64_C(184467440738);
2339 auto s = size_t(b);
2340 significand = b ? r : significand;
2341
2342 r = rotr(uint64_t(significand * UINT64_C(182622766329724561)), 4);
2343 b = r < UINT64_C(1844674407370956);
2344 s = s * 2 + b;
2345 significand = b ? r : significand;
2346
2347 r = rotr(uint64_t(significand * UINT64_C(10330176681277348905)), 2);
2348 b = r < UINT64_C(184467440737095517);
2349 s = s * 2 + b;
2350 significand = b ? r : significand;
2351
2352 r = rotr(uint64_t(significand * UINT64_C(14757395258967641293)), 1);
2353 b = r < UINT64_C(1844674407370955162);
2354 s = s * 2 + b;
2355 significand = b ? r : significand;
2356
2357 exponent += s;
2358 }
2359};

2361template <class DecimalExponentType>
2362struct remove_trailing_zeros_traits<policy::trailing_zero::remove_compact_t, ieee754_binary32,
2363 uint32_t, DecimalExponentType> {
2364 WJR_INTRINSIC_INLINE static constexpr void
2365 remove_trailing_zeros(uint32_t &significand, DecimalExponentType &exponent) noexcept {
2366 // See https://github.com/jk-jeon/rtz_benchmark.
2367 while (true) {
2368 auto const r = uint32_t(significand * UINT32_C(1288490189));
2369 if (r < UINT32_C(429496731)) {
2370 significand = uint32_t(r >> 1);
2371 exponent += 1;
2372 } else {
2373 break;
2374 }
2375 }
2376 }
2377};

2379template <class DecimalExponentType>
2380struct remove_trailing_zeros_traits<policy::trailing_zero::remove_compact_t, ieee754_binary64,
2381 uint64_t, DecimalExponentType> {
2382 WJR_INTRINSIC_INLINE static constexpr void
2383 remove_trailing_zeros(uint64_t &significand, DecimalExponentType &exponent) noexcept {
2384 // See https://github.com/jk-jeon/rtz_benchmark.
2385 while (true) {
2386 auto const r = uint64_t(significand * UINT64_C(5534023222112865485));
2387 if (r < UINT64_C(1844674407370955163)) {
2388 significand = uint64_t(r >> 1);
2389 exponent += 1;
2390 } else {
2391 break;
2392 }
2393 }
2394 }

2397template <class ExponentInt>
2398struct multiplication_traits<ieee754_binary_traits<ieee754_binary32, uint32_t, ExponentInt>,
2399 uint64_t, 64>
2400 : public multiplication_traits_base<ieee754_binary_traits<ieee754_binary32, uint32_t>, uint64_t,
2401 64> {
2402 static WJR_INTRINSIC_CONSTEXPR20 compute_mul_result
2403 compute_mul(carrier_uint u, cache_entry_type const &cache) noexcept {
2404 auto const r = detail::wuint::umul96_upper64(u, cache);
2405 return {carrier_uint(r >> 32), carrier_uint(r) == 0};
2406 }
2407
2408 template <class ShiftAmountType>
2409 static constexpr uint64_t compute_delta(cache_entry_type const &cache,
2410 ShiftAmountType beta) noexcept {
2411 return uint64_t(cache >> ShiftAmountType(cache_bits - 1 - beta));
2412 }
2413
2414 template <class ShiftAmountType>
2415 static WJR_INTRINSIC_CONSTEXPR20 compute_mul_parity_result compute_mul_parity(
2416 carrier_uint two_f, cache_entry_type const &cache, ShiftAmountType beta) noexcept {
2417 WJR_ASSERT(beta >= 1);
2418 WJR_ASSERT(beta <= 32);
2419
2420 auto const r = detail::wuint::umul96_lower64(two_f, cache);
2421 return {((r >> ShiftAmountType(64 - beta)) & 1) != 0,
2422 (UINT32_C(0xffffffff) & (r >> ShiftAmountType(32 - beta))) == 0};
2423 }
2424
2425 template <class ShiftAmountType>
2426 static constexpr carrier_uint
2427 compute_left_endpoint_for_shorter_interval_case(cache_entry_type const &cache,
2428 ShiftAmountType beta) noexcept {
2429 return carrier_uint((cache - (cache >> (significand_bits + 2))) >>
2430 ShiftAmountType(cache_bits - significand_bits - 1 - beta));
2431 }
2432
2433 template <class ShiftAmountType>
2434 static constexpr carrier_uint
2435 compute_right_endpoint_for_shorter_interval_case(cache_entry_type const &cache,
2436 ShiftAmountType beta) noexcept {
2437 return carrier_uint((cache + (cache >> (significand_bits + 1))) >>
2438 ShiftAmountType(cache_bits - significand_bits - 1 - beta));
2439 }
2440
2441 template <class ShiftAmountType>
2442 static constexpr carrier_uint
2443 compute_round_up_for_shorter_interval_case(cache_entry_type const &cache,
2444 ShiftAmountType beta) noexcept {
2445 return (carrier_uint(cache >> ShiftAmountType(cache_bits - significand_bits - 2 - beta)) +
2446 1) /
2447 2;
2448 }
2449};

2451template <class ExponentInt>
2452struct multiplication_traits<ieee754_binary_traits<ieee754_binary64, uint64_t, ExponentInt>,
2453 uint128_t, 128>
2454 : public multiplication_traits_base<ieee754_binary_traits<ieee754_binary64, uint64_t>,
2455 uint128_t, 128> {
2456 static WJR_INTRINSIC_CONSTEXPR20 compute_mul_result
2457 compute_mul(carrier_uint u, cache_entry_type const &cache) noexcept {
2458 auto const r = detail::wuint::umul192_upper128(u, cache);
2459 return {r.high, r.low == 0};
2460 }
2461
2462 template <class ShiftAmountType>
2463 static constexpr uint64_t compute_delta(cache_entry_type const &cache,
2464 ShiftAmountType beta) noexcept {
2465 return uint64_t(cache.high >> ShiftAmountType(total_bits - 1 - beta));
2466 }
2467
2468 template <class ShiftAmountType>
2469 static WJR_INTRINSIC_CONSTEXPR20 compute_mul_parity_result compute_mul_parity(
2470 carrier_uint two_f, cache_entry_type const &cache, ShiftAmountType beta) noexcept {
2471 WJR_ASSERT(beta >= 1);
2472 WJR_ASSERT(beta < 64);
2473
2474 auto const r = detail::wuint::umul192_lower128(two_f, cache);
2475 return {((r.high >> ShiftAmountType(64 - beta)) & 1) != 0,
2476 (((r.high << beta) & UINT64_C(0xffffffffffffffff)) |
2477 (r.low >> ShiftAmountType(64 - beta))) == 0};
2478 }
2479
2480 template <class ShiftAmountType>
2481 static constexpr carrier_uint
2482 compute_left_endpoint_for_shorter_interval_case(cache_entry_type const &cache,
2483 ShiftAmountType beta) noexcept {
2484 return (cache.high - (cache.high >> (significand_bits + 2))) >>
2485 ShiftAmountType(total_bits - significand_bits - 1 - beta);
2486 }
2487
2488 template <class ShiftAmountType>
2489 static constexpr carrier_uint
2490 compute_right_endpoint_for_shorter_interval_case(cache_entry_type const &cache,
2491 ShiftAmountType beta) noexcept {
2492 return (cache.high + (cache.high >> (significand_bits + 1))) >>
2493 ShiftAmountType(total_bits - significand_bits - 1 - beta);
2494 }
2495
2496 template <class ShiftAmountType>
2497 static constexpr carrier_uint
2498 compute_round_up_for_shorter_interval_case(cache_entry_type const &cache,
2499 ShiftAmountType beta) noexcept {
2500 return ((cache.high >> ShiftAmountType(total_bits - significand_bits - 2 - beta)) + 1) / 2;
2501 }
2502};

2504namespace detail {
2506// The main algorithm.
2508
2509template <class FormatTraits>
2510struct impl : private FormatTraits::format {
2511 using format = typename FormatTraits::format;
2512 using carrier_uint = typename FormatTraits::carrier_uint;
2513 static constexpr int carrier_bits = FormatTraits::carrier_bits;
2514 using exponent_int = typename FormatTraits::exponent_int;
2515
2516 using format::exponent_bias;
2517 using format::max_exponent;
2518 using format::min_exponent;
2519 using format::significand_bits;
2520
2521 static constexpr int kappa = log::floor_log10_pow2(carrier_bits - significand_bits - 2) - 1;
2522 static_assert(kappa >= 1);
2523 static_assert(carrier_bits >= significand_bits + 2 + log::floor_log2_pow10(kappa + 1), "");
2524
2525 static constexpr int min(int x, int y) noexcept { return x < y ? x : y; }
2526 static constexpr int max(int x, int y) noexcept { return x > y ? x : y; }
2527
2528 static constexpr int min_k =
2529 min(-log::floor_log10_pow2_minus_log10_4_over_3(max_exponent - significand_bits),
2530 -log::floor_log10_pow2(max_exponent - significand_bits) + kappa);
2531
2532 // We do invoke shorter_interval_case for exponent == min_exponent case,
2533 // so we should not add 1 here.
2534 static constexpr int max_k =
2535 max(-log::floor_log10_pow2_minus_log10_4_over_3(min_exponent - significand_bits /*+ 1*/),
2536 -log::floor_log10_pow2(min_exponent - significand_bits) + kappa);
2537
2538 static constexpr int case_shorter_interval_left_endpoint_lower_threshold = 2;
2539 static constexpr int case_shorter_interval_left_endpoint_upper_threshold =
2540 2 +
2541 log::floor_log2(
2542 compute_power<count_factors<5>((carrier_uint(1) << (significand_bits + 2)) - 1) + 1>(
2543 10) /
2544 3);
2545
2546 static constexpr int case_shorter_interval_right_endpoint_lower_threshold = 0;
2547 static constexpr int case_shorter_interval_right_endpoint_upper_threshold =
2548 2 +
2549 log::floor_log2(
2550 compute_power<count_factors<5>((carrier_uint(1) << (significand_bits + 1)) + 1) + 1>(
2551 10) /
2552 3);
2553
2554 static constexpr int shorter_interval_tie_lower_threshold =
2555 -log::floor_log5_pow2_minus_log5_3(significand_bits + 4) - 2 - significand_bits;
2556 static constexpr int shorter_interval_tie_upper_threshold =
2557 -log::floor_log5_pow2(significand_bits + 2) - 2 - significand_bits;
2558
2559 template <class PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>
2560 using remainder_type = typename PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy::template remainder_type<
2561 FormatTraits, compute_power<kappa + 1>(uint64_t(10))>;
2562
2563 template <class PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>
2564 using decimal_exponent_type =
2565 typename PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy::template decimal_exponent_type<
2566 FormatTraits, std::int32_t(min(-max_k, min_k)),
2567 std::int32_t(max(max_k, -min_k + kappa + 1))>;
2568
2569 template <class SignPolicy, class TrailingZeroPolicy, class PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>
2570 using return_type =
2571 decimal_fp<carrier_uint, decimal_exponent_type<PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>,
2572 SignPolicy::return_has_sign, TrailingZeroPolicy::report_trailing_zeros>;
2573
2576
2577 template <class SignPolicy, class TrailingZeroPolicy, class IntervalTypeProvider,
2578 class BinaryToDecimalRoundingPolicy, class CachePolicy,
2579 class PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>
2580 WJR_SAFEBUFFERS static WJR_CONSTEXPR20
2581 return_type<SignPolicy, TrailingZeroPolicy, PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>
2582 compute_nearest(signed_significand_bits<FormatTraits> s,
2583 exponent_int exponent_bits) noexcept {
2584 using cache_holder_type = typename CachePolicy::template cache_holder_type<format>;
2585 static_assert(min_k >= cache_holder_type::min_k && max_k <= cache_holder_type::max_k);
2586
2587 using remainder_type_ = remainder_type<PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>;
2588 using decimal_exponent_type_ = decimal_exponent_type<PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>;
2589 using shift_amount_type =
2590 typename PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy::template shift_amount_type<FormatTraits>;
2591
2592 using multiplication_traits_ =
2593 multiplication_traits<FormatTraits, typename cache_holder_type::cache_entry_type,
2594 cache_holder_type::cache_bits>;
2595
2596 auto two_fc = s.remove_sign_bit_and_shift();
2597 auto binary_exponent = exponent_bits;
2598
2599 // Is the input a normal number?
2600 if (binary_exponent != 0) {
2601 binary_exponent += format::exponent_bias - format::significand_bits;
2602
2603 // Shorter interval case; proceed like Schubfach.
2604 // One might think this condition is wrong, since when exponent_bits
2605 // == 1 and two_fc == 0, the interval is actually regular. However,
2606 // it turns out that this seemingly wrong condition is actually
2607 // fine, because the end result is anyway the same.
2608 //
2609 // [binary32]
2610 // (fc-1/2) * 2^e = 1.175'494'28... * 10^-38
2611 // (fc-1/4) * 2^e = 1.175'494'31... * 10^-38
2612 // fc * 2^e = 1.175'494'35... * 10^-38
2613 // (fc+1/2) * 2^e = 1.175'494'42... * 10^-38
2614 //
2615 // Hence, shorter_interval_case will return 1.175'494'4 * 10^-38.
2616 // 1.175'494'3 * 10^-38 is also a correct shortest representation
2617 // that will be rejected if we assume shorter interval,
2618 // but 1.175'494'4 * 10^-38 is closer to the true value so it
2619 // doesn't matter.
2620 //
2621 // [binary64]
2622 // (fc-1/2) * 2^e = 2.225'073'858'507'201'13... * 10^-308
2623 // (fc-1/4) * 2^e = 2.225'073'858'507'201'25... * 10^-308
2624 // fc * 2^e = 2.225'073'858'507'201'38... * 10^-308
2625 // (fc+1/2) * 2^e = 2.225'073'858'507'201'63... * 10^-308
2626 //
2627 // Hence, shorter_interval_case will return 2.225'073'858'507'201'4
2628 // * 10^-308. This is indeed of the shortest length, and it is the
2629 // unique one closest to the true value among valid representations
2630 // of the same length.
2631 static_assert(std::is_same<format, ieee754_binary32>::value ||
2632 std::is_same<format, ieee754_binary64>::value,
2633 "");
2634
2635 // Shorter interval case.
2636 if (two_fc == 0) {
2637 auto interval_type = IntervalTypeProvider::shorter_interval(s);
2638
2639 // Compute k and beta.
2640 auto const minus_k = log::floor_log10_pow2_minus_log10_4_over_3<
2641 min_exponent - format::significand_bits,
2642 max_exponent - format::significand_bits, decimal_exponent_type_>(
2643 binary_exponent);
2644 auto const beta =
2645 shift_amount_type(binary_exponent + log::floor_log2_pow10<min_k, max_k>(
2646 decimal_exponent_type_(-minus_k)));
2647
2648 // Compute xi and zi.
2649 auto const cache = CachePolicy::template get_cache<format, shift_amount_type>(
2650 decimal_exponent_type_(-minus_k));
2651
2652 auto xi = multiplication_traits_::compute_left_endpoint_for_shorter_interval_case(
2653 cache, beta);
2654 auto zi = multiplication_traits_::compute_right_endpoint_for_shorter_interval_case(
2655 cache, beta);
2656
2657 // If we don't accept the right endpoint and
2658 // if the right endpoint is an integer, decrease it.
2659 if (!interval_type.include_right_endpoint() &&
2660 is_right_endpoint_integer_shorter_interval(binary_exponent)) {
2661 --zi;
2662 }
2663 // If we don't accept the left endpoint or
2664 // if the left endpoint is not an integer, increase it.
2665 if (!interval_type.include_left_endpoint() ||
2666 !is_left_endpoint_integer_shorter_interval(binary_exponent)) {
2667 ++xi;
2668 }
2669
2670 // Try bigger divisor.
2671 // zi is at most floor((f_c + 1/2) * 2^e * 10^k0).
2672 // Substituting f_c = 2^p and k0 = -floor(log10(3 * 2^(e-2))),
2673 // we get zi <= floor((2^(p+1) + 1) * 20/3) <= ceil((2^(p+1) +
2674 // 1)/3) * 20. This computation does not overflow for any of the
2675 // formats I care about.
2676 carrier_uint decimal_significand = div::divide_by_pow10<
2677 1, carrier_uint,
2678 carrier_uint(((((carrier_uint(1) << (significand_bits + 1)) + 1) / 3) + 1) *
2679 20)>(zi);
2680
2681 // If succeed, remove trailing zeros if necessary and return.
2682 if (decimal_significand * 10 >= xi) {
2683 return SignPolicy::handle_sign(
2684 s, TrailingZeroPolicy::template on_trailing_zeros<format>(
2685 decimal_significand, decimal_exponent_type_(minus_k + 1)));
2686 }
2687
2688 // Otherwise, compute the round-up of y.
2689 decimal_significand =
2690 multiplication_traits_::compute_round_up_for_shorter_interval_case(cache, beta);
2691
2692 // When tie occurs, choose one of them according to the rule.
2693 if (BinaryToDecimalRoundingPolicy::prefer_round_down(decimal_significand) &&
2694 binary_exponent >= shorter_interval_tie_lower_threshold &&
2695 binary_exponent <= shorter_interval_tie_upper_threshold) {
2696 --decimal_significand;
2697 } else if (decimal_significand < xi) {
2698 ++decimal_significand;
2699 }
2700 return SignPolicy::handle_sign(
2701 s, TrailingZeroPolicy::template no_trailing_zeros<format>(
2702 decimal_significand, decimal_exponent_type_(minus_k)));
2703 }
2704
2705 // Normal interval case.
2706 two_fc |= (carrier_uint(1) << (format::significand_bits + 1));
2707 }
2708 // Is the input a subnormal number?
2709 else {
2710 // Normal interval case.
2711 binary_exponent = format::min_exponent - format::significand_bits;
2712 }
2713
2715 // Step 1: Schubfach multiplier calculation.
2717
2718 auto interval_type = IntervalTypeProvider::normal_interval(s);
2719
2720 // Compute k and beta.
2721 auto const minus_k = decimal_exponent_type_(
2722 log::floor_log10_pow2<min_exponent - format::significand_bits,
2723 max_exponent - format::significand_bits, decimal_exponent_type_>(
2724 binary_exponent) -
2725 kappa);
2726 auto const cache = CachePolicy::template get_cache<format, shift_amount_type>(
2727 decimal_exponent_type_(-minus_k));
2728 auto const beta =
2729 shift_amount_type(binary_exponent + log::floor_log2_pow10<min_k, max_k>(
2730 decimal_exponent_type_(-minus_k)));
2731
2732 // Compute zi and deltai.
2733 // 10^kappa <= deltai < 10^(kappa + 1)
2734 auto const deltai =
2735 static_cast<remainder_type_>(multiplication_traits_::compute_delta(cache, beta));
2736 // For the case of binary32, the result of integer check is not correct
2737 // for 29711844 * 2^-82
2738 // = 6.1442653300000000008655037797566933477355632930994033813476... *
2739 // 10^-18 and 29711844 * 2^-81
2740 // = 1.2288530660000000001731007559513386695471126586198806762695... *
2741 // 10^-17, and they are the unique counterexamples. However, since
2742 // 29711844 is even, this does not cause any problem for the endpoints
2743 // calculations; it can only cause a problem when we need to perform
2744 // integer check for the center. Fortunately, with these inputs, that
2745 // branch is never executed, so we are fine.
2746 auto const z_result =
2747 multiplication_traits_::compute_mul(carrier_uint((two_fc | 1) << beta), cache);
2748
2750 // Step 2: Try larger divisor; remove trailing zeros if necessary.
2752
2753 constexpr auto big_divisor = compute_power<kappa + 1>(remainder_type_(10));
2754 constexpr auto small_divisor = compute_power<kappa>(remainder_type_(10));
2755
2756 // Using an upper bound on zi, we might be able to optimize the division
2757 // better than the compiler; we are computing zi / big_divisor here.
2758 carrier_uint decimal_significand = div::divide_by_pow10<
2759 kappa + 1, carrier_uint,
2760 carrier_uint((carrier_uint(1) << (significand_bits + 1)) * big_divisor - 1)>(
2761 z_result.integer_part);
2762 auto r = remainder_type_(z_result.integer_part - big_divisor * decimal_significand);
2763
2764 do {
2765 if (r < deltai) {
2766 // Exclude the right endpoint if necessary.
2767 if ((r | remainder_type_(!z_result.is_integer) |
2768 remainder_type_(interval_type.include_right_endpoint())) == 0) {
2769 if constexpr (BinaryToDecimalRoundingPolicy::tag ==
2770 policy::binary_to_decimal_rounding::tag_t::do_not_care) {
2771 decimal_significand *= 10;
2772 --decimal_significand;
2773 return SignPolicy::handle_sign(
2774 s, TrailingZeroPolicy::template no_trailing_zeros<format>(
2775 decimal_significand, decimal_exponent_type_(minus_k + kappa)));
2776 } else {
2777 --decimal_significand;
2778 r = big_divisor;
2779 break;
2780 }
2781 }
2782 } else if (r > deltai) {
2783 break;
2784 } else {
2785 // r == deltai; compare fractional parts.
2786 auto const x_result = multiplication_traits_::compute_mul_parity(
2787 carrier_uint(two_fc - 1), cache, beta);
2788
2789 if (!(x_result.parity |
2790 (x_result.is_integer & interval_type.include_left_endpoint()))) {
2791 break;
2792 }
2793 }
2794
2795 // We may need to remove trailing zeros.
2796 return SignPolicy::handle_sign(
2797 s, TrailingZeroPolicy::template on_trailing_zeros<format>(
2798 decimal_significand, decimal_exponent_type_(minus_k + kappa + 1)));
2799 } while (0);
2800
2802 // Step 3: Find the significand with the smaller divisor.
2804
2805 decimal_significand *= 10;
2806
2807 if constexpr (BinaryToDecimalRoundingPolicy::tag ==
2808 policy::binary_to_decimal_rounding::tag_t::do_not_care) {
2809 // Normally, we want to compute
2810 // significand += r / small_divisor
2811 // and return, but we need to take care of the case that the
2812 // resulting value is exactly the right endpoint, while that is not
2813 // included in the interval.
2814 if (!interval_type.include_right_endpoint()) {
2815 // Is r divisible by 10^kappa?
2816 if (div::check_divisibility_and_divide_by_pow10<kappa>(r) && z_result.is_integer) {
2817 // This should be in the interval.
2818 decimal_significand += r - 1;
2819 } else {
2820 decimal_significand += r;
2821 }
2822 } else {
2823 decimal_significand += div::small_division_by_pow10<kappa>(r);
2824 }
2825 } else {
2826 // delta is equal to 10^(kappa + elog10(2) - floor(elog10(2))), so
2827 // dist cannot be larger than r.
2828 auto dist = remainder_type_(r - (deltai / 2) + (small_divisor / 2));
2829 bool const approx_y_parity = ((dist ^ (small_divisor / 2)) & 1) != 0;
2830
2831 // Is dist divisible by 10^kappa?
2832 bool const divisible_by_small_divisor =
2833 div::check_divisibility_and_divide_by_pow10<kappa>(dist);
2834
2835 // Add dist / 10^kappa to the significand.
2836 decimal_significand += dist;
2837
2838 if (divisible_by_small_divisor) {
2839 // Check z^(f) >= epsilon^(f).
2840 // We have either yi == zi - epsiloni or yi == (zi - epsiloni) -
2841 // 1, where yi == zi - epsiloni if and only if z^(f) >=
2842 // epsilon^(f). Since there are only 2 possibilities, we only
2843 // need to care about the parity. Also, zi and r should have the
2844 // same parity since the divisor is an even number.
2845 auto const y_result =
2846 multiplication_traits_::compute_mul_parity(two_fc, cache, beta);
2847 if (y_result.parity != approx_y_parity) {
2848 --decimal_significand;
2849 } else {
2850 // If z^(f) >= epsilon^(f), we might have a tie
2851 // when z^(f) == epsilon^(f), or equivalently, when y is an
2852 // integer. For tie-to-up case, we can just choose the upper
2853 // one.
2854 if (BinaryToDecimalRoundingPolicy::prefer_round_down(decimal_significand) &
2855 y_result.is_integer) {
2856 --decimal_significand;
2857 }
2858 }
2859 }
2860 }
2861 return SignPolicy::handle_sign(
2862 s, TrailingZeroPolicy::template no_trailing_zeros<format>(
2863 decimal_significand, decimal_exponent_type_(minus_k + kappa)));
2864 }
2865
2866 template <class SignPolicy, class TrailingZeroPolicy, class CachePolicy,
2867 class PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>
2868 WJR_INTRINSIC_INLINE WJR_SAFEBUFFERS static WJR_CONSTEXPR20
2869 return_type<SignPolicy, TrailingZeroPolicy, PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>
2870 compute_left_closed_directed(signed_significand_bits<FormatTraits> s,
2871 exponent_int exponent_bits) noexcept {
2872 using cache_holder_type = typename CachePolicy::template cache_holder_type<format>;
2873 static_assert(min_k >= cache_holder_type::min_k && max_k <= cache_holder_type::max_k);
2874
2875 using remainder_type_ = remainder_type<PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>;
2876 using decimal_exponent_type_ = decimal_exponent_type<PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>;
2877 using shift_amount_type =
2878 typename PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy::template shift_amount_type<FormatTraits>;
2879
2880 using multiplication_traits_ =
2881 multiplication_traits<FormatTraits, typename cache_holder_type::cache_entry_type,
2882 cache_holder_type::cache_bits>;
2883
2884 auto two_fc = s.remove_sign_bit_and_shift();
2885 auto binary_exponent = exponent_bits;
2886
2887 // Is the input a normal number?
2888 if (binary_exponent != 0) {
2889 binary_exponent += format::exponent_bias - format::significand_bits;
2890 two_fc |= (carrier_uint(1) << (format::significand_bits + 1));
2891 }
2892 // Is the input a subnormal number?
2893 else {
2894 binary_exponent = format::min_exponent - format::significand_bits;
2895 }
2896
2898 // Step 1: Schubfach multiplier calculation.
2900
2901 // Compute k and beta.
2902 auto const minus_k = decimal_exponent_type_(
2903 log::floor_log10_pow2<format::min_exponent - format::significand_bits,
2904 format::max_exponent - format::significand_bits,
2905 decimal_exponent_type_>(binary_exponent) -
2906 kappa);
2907 auto const cache = CachePolicy::template get_cache<format, shift_amount_type>(
2908 decimal_exponent_type_(-minus_k));
2909 auto const beta =
2910 shift_amount_type(binary_exponent + log::floor_log2_pow10<min_k, max_k>(
2911 decimal_exponent_type_(-minus_k)));
2912
2913 // Compute xi and deltai.
2914 // 10^kappa <= deltai < 10^(kappa + 1)
2915 auto const deltai =
2916 static_cast<remainder_type_>(multiplication_traits_::compute_delta(cache, beta));
2917 auto x_result = multiplication_traits_::compute_mul(carrier_uint(two_fc << beta), cache);
2918
2919 // Deal with the unique exceptional cases
2920 // 29711844 * 2^-82
2921 // = 6.1442653300000000008655037797566933477355632930994033813476... *
2922 // 10^-18 and 29711844 * 2^-81
2923 // = 1.2288530660000000001731007559513386695471126586198806762695... *
2924 // 10^-17 for binary32.
2925 if constexpr (std::is_same<format, ieee754_binary32>::value) {
2926 if (binary_exponent <= -80) {
2927 x_result.is_integer = false;
2928 }
2929 }
2930
2931 if (!x_result.is_integer) {
2932 ++x_result.integer_part;
2933 }
2934
2936 // Step 2: Try larger divisor; remove trailing zeros if necessary.
2938
2939 constexpr auto big_divisor = compute_power<kappa + 1>(remainder_type_(10));
2940
2941 // Using an upper bound on xi, we might be able to optimize the division
2942 // better than the compiler; we are computing xi / big_divisor here.
2943 carrier_uint decimal_significand = div::divide_by_pow10<
2944 kappa + 1, carrier_uint,
2945 carrier_uint((carrier_uint(1) << (significand_bits + 1)) * big_divisor - 1)>(
2946 x_result.integer_part);
2947 auto r = remainder_type_(x_result.integer_part - big_divisor * decimal_significand);
2948
2949 if (r != 0) {
2950 ++decimal_significand;
2951 r = remainder_type_(big_divisor - r);
2952 }
2953
2954 do {
2955 if (r > deltai) {
2956 break;
2957 } else if (r == deltai) {
2958 // Compare the fractional parts.
2959 // This branch is never taken for the exceptional cases
2960 // 2f_c = 29711482, e = -81
2961 // (6.1442649164096937243516663440523473127541365101933479309082...
2962 // * 10^-18) and 2f_c = 29711482, e = -80
2963 // (1.2288529832819387448703332688104694625508273020386695861816...
2964 // * 10^-17). For the case of compressed cache for binary32,
2965 // there is another exceptional case 2f_c = 33554430, e = -10
2966 // (16383.9990234375). In this case, the recovered cache is two
2967 // large to make compute_mul_parity mistakenly conclude that z
2968 // is not an integer, but actually z = 16384 is an integer.
2969 if constexpr (std::is_same<cache_holder_type,
2970 compressed_cache_holder<ieee754_binary32>>::value) {
2971 if (two_fc == 33554430 && binary_exponent == -10) {
2972 break;
2973 }
2974 }
2975 auto const z_result = multiplication_traits_::compute_mul_parity(
2976 carrier_uint(two_fc + 2), cache, beta);
2977 if (z_result.parity || z_result.is_integer) {
2978 break;
2979 }
2980 }
2981
2982 // The ceiling is inside, so we are done.
2983 return SignPolicy::handle_sign(
2984 s, TrailingZeroPolicy::template on_trailing_zeros<format>(
2985 decimal_significand, decimal_exponent_type_(minus_k + kappa + 1)));
2986 } while (0);
2987
2989 // Step 3: Find the significand with the smaller divisor.
2991
2992 decimal_significand *= 10;
2993 decimal_significand -= div::small_division_by_pow10<kappa>(r);
2994 return SignPolicy::handle_sign(
2995 s, TrailingZeroPolicy::template no_trailing_zeros<format>(
2996 decimal_significand, decimal_exponent_type_(minus_k + kappa)));
2997 }
2998
2999 template <class SignPolicy, class TrailingZeroPolicy, class CachePolicy,
3000 class PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>
3001 WJR_INTRINSIC_INLINE WJR_SAFEBUFFERS static WJR_CONSTEXPR20
3002 return_type<SignPolicy, TrailingZeroPolicy, PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>
3003 compute_right_closed_directed(signed_significand_bits<FormatTraits> s,
3004 exponent_int exponent_bits) noexcept {
3005 using cache_holder_type = typename CachePolicy::template cache_holder_type<format>;
3006 static_assert(min_k >= cache_holder_type::min_k && max_k <= cache_holder_type::max_k);
3007
3008 using remainder_type_ = remainder_type<PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>;
3009 using decimal_exponent_type_ = decimal_exponent_type<PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>;
3010 using shift_amount_type =
3011 typename PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy::template shift_amount_type<FormatTraits>;
3012
3013 using multiplication_traits_ =
3014 multiplication_traits<FormatTraits, typename cache_holder_type::cache_entry_type,
3015 cache_holder_type::cache_bits>;
3016
3017 auto two_fc = s.remove_sign_bit_and_shift();
3018 auto binary_exponent = exponent_bits;
3019 bool shorter_interval = false;
3020
3021 // Is the input a normal number?
3022 if (binary_exponent != 0) {
3023 if (two_fc == 0 && binary_exponent != 1) {
3024 shorter_interval = true;
3025 }
3026 binary_exponent += format::exponent_bias - format::significand_bits;
3027 two_fc |= (carrier_uint(1) << (format::significand_bits + 1));
3028 }
3029 // Is the input a subnormal number?
3030 else {
3031 binary_exponent = format::min_exponent - format::significand_bits;
3032 }
3033
3035 // Step 1: Schubfach multiplier calculation.
3037
3038 // Compute k and beta.
3039 auto const minus_k = decimal_exponent_type_(
3040 log::floor_log10_pow2<format::min_exponent - format::significand_bits,
3041 format::max_exponent - format::significand_bits,
3042 decimal_exponent_type_>(
3043 exponent_int(binary_exponent - (shorter_interval ? 1 : 0))) -
3044 kappa);
3045 auto const cache = CachePolicy::template get_cache<format, shift_amount_type>(
3046 decimal_exponent_type_(-minus_k));
3047 auto const beta = shift_amount_type(
3048 binary_exponent + log::floor_log2_pow10(decimal_exponent_type_(-minus_k)));
3049
3050 // Compute zi and deltai.
3051 // 10^kappa <= deltai < 10^(kappa + 1)
3052 auto const deltai = static_cast<remainder_type_>(multiplication_traits_::compute_delta(
3053 cache, shift_amount_type(beta - (shorter_interval ? 1 : 0))));
3054 carrier_uint const zi =
3055 multiplication_traits_::compute_mul(carrier_uint(two_fc << beta), cache).integer_part;
3056
3058 // Step 2: Try larger divisor; remove trailing zeros if necessary.
3060
3061 constexpr auto big_divisor = compute_power<kappa + 1>(remainder_type_(10));
3062
3063 // Using an upper bound on zi, we might be able to optimize the division
3064 // better than the compiler; we are computing zi / big_divisor here.
3065 carrier_uint decimal_significand = div::divide_by_pow10<
3066 kappa + 1, carrier_uint,
3067 carrier_uint((carrier_uint(1) << (significand_bits + 1)) * big_divisor - 1)>(zi);
3068 auto const r = remainder_type_(zi - big_divisor * decimal_significand);
3069
3070 do {
3071 if (r > deltai) {
3072 break;
3073 } else if (r == deltai) {
3074 // Compare the fractional parts.
3075 if (!multiplication_traits_::compute_mul_parity(
3076 carrier_uint(two_fc - (shorter_interval ? 1 : 2)), cache, beta)
3077 .parity) {
3078 break;
3079 }
3080 }
3081
3082 // The floor is inside, so we are done.
3083 return SignPolicy::handle_sign(
3084 s, TrailingZeroPolicy::template on_trailing_zeros<format>(
3085 decimal_significand, decimal_exponent_type_(minus_k + kappa + 1)));
3086 } while (0);
3087
3089 // Step 3: Find the significand with the small divisor.
3091
3092 decimal_significand *= 10;
3093 decimal_significand += div::small_division_by_pow10<kappa>(r);
3094 return SignPolicy::handle_sign(
3095 s, TrailingZeroPolicy::template no_trailing_zeros<format>(
3096 decimal_significand, decimal_exponent_type_(minus_k + kappa)));
3097 }

3113// Policy holder.
3115
3116// The library will specify a list of accepted kinds of policies and their
3117// defaults, and the user will pass a list of policies parameters. The policy
3118// parameters are supposed to be stateless and only convey information through
3119// their types. The aim of the helper classes/functions given below is to do the
3120// following:
3121// 1. Check if the policy parameters given by the user are all valid; that
3122// means,
3123// each of them should be at least of one of the kinds specified by the
3124// library. If that's not the case, then the compilation fails.
3125// 2. Check if multiple policy parameters for the same kind is specified by
3126// the
3127// user. If that's the case, then the compilation fails.
3128// 3. Build a class deriving from all policies the user have given, and also
3129// from
3130// the default policies if the user did not specify one for some kinds.
3131// The library considers a certain policy parameter to belong to a specific kind
3132// if and only if the parameter's type has a member type with a specific name;
3133// for example, it belongs to "sign policy" kind if there is a member type
3134// sign_policy.
3135
3136// For a given kind, find a policy belonging to that kind.
3137// Check if there are more than one such policies.
3138enum class policy_found_info { not_found, unique, repeated };
3139template <class Policy, policy_found_info info>
3140struct found_policy_pair {
3141 // Either the policy parameter type given by the user, or the default
3142 // policy.
3143 using policy = Policy;
3144 static constexpr auto found_info = info;
3145};
3146
3147template <class KindDetector, class DefaultPolicy>
3148struct detector_default_pair {
3149 using kind_detector = KindDetector;
3150
3151 // Iterate through all given policy parameter types and see if there is a
3152 // policy parameter type belonging to the policy kind specified by
3153 // KindDetector.
3154 // 1. If there is none, get_found_policy_pair returns
3155 // found_policy_pair<DefaultPolicy, policy_found_info::not_found>.
3156 // 2. If there is only one parameter type belonging to the specified kind,
3157 // then
3158 // get_found_policy_pair returns
3159 // found_policy_pair<Policy, policy_found_info::unique>
3160 // where Policy is the unique parameter type belonging to the specified
3161 // kind.
3162 // 3. If there are multiple parameter types belonging to the specified kind,
3163 // then
3164 // get_found_policy_pair returns
3165 // found_policy_pair<FirstPolicy, policy_found_info::repeated>
3166 // where FirstPolicy is the first parameter type belonging to the
3167 // specified kind. The compilation must fail if this happens.
3168 // This is done by first setting FoundPolicyInfo below to
3169 // found_policy_pair<DefaultPolicy, policy_found_info::not_found>, and then
3170 // iterate over Policies, replacing FoundPolicyInfo by the appropriate one
3171 // if a parameter type belonging to the specified kind is found.
3172
3173 template <class FoundPolicyInfo, class... Policies>
3174 struct get_found_policy_pair_impl;
3175
3176 template <class FoundPolicyInfo>
3177 struct get_found_policy_pair_impl<FoundPolicyInfo> {
3178 using type = FoundPolicyInfo;
3179 };
3180
3181 template <class FoundPolicyInfo, class FirstPolicy, class... RemainingPolicies>
3182 struct get_found_policy_pair_impl<FoundPolicyInfo, FirstPolicy, RemainingPolicies...> {
3183 using type = typename std::conditional<
3184 KindDetector{}(dummy<FirstPolicy>{}),
3185 typename std::conditional<
3186 FoundPolicyInfo::found_info == policy_found_info::not_found,
3187 typename get_found_policy_pair_impl<
3188 found_policy_pair<FirstPolicy, policy_found_info::unique>,
3189 RemainingPolicies...>::type,
3190 typename get_found_policy_pair_impl<
3191 found_policy_pair<FirstPolicy, policy_found_info::repeated>,
3192 RemainingPolicies...>::type>::type,
3193 typename get_found_policy_pair_impl<FoundPolicyInfo, RemainingPolicies...>::type>::type;
3194 };
3195
3196 template <class... Policies>
3197 using get_found_policy_pair = typename get_found_policy_pair_impl<
3198 found_policy_pair<DefaultPolicy, policy_found_info::not_found>, Policies...>::type;
3199};

3382 detector_default_pair<is_cache_policy, policy::cache::full_t>,
3383 detector_default_pair<is_preferred_integer_types_policy,
3384 policy::preferred_integer_types::match_t>>,
3385 Policies...>;
3386
3387template <class FormatTraits, class... Policies>
3388using to_decimal_return_type = typename impl<FormatTraits>::template return_type<
3389 typename to_decimal_policy_holder<Policies...>::sign_policy,
3390 typename to_decimal_policy_holder<Policies...>::trailing_zero_policy,
3391 typename to_decimal_policy_holder<Policies...>::preferred_integer_types_policy>;
3392
3393template <class FormatTraits, class PolicyHolder>
3394struct to_decimal_dispatcher {
3395 using sign_policy = typename PolicyHolder::sign_policy;
3396 using trailing_zero_policy = typename PolicyHolder::trailing_zero_policy;
3397 using binary_to_decimal_rounding_policy =
3398 typename PolicyHolder::binary_to_decimal_rounding_policy;
3399 using cache_policy = typename PolicyHolder::cache_policy;
3400 using preferred_integer_types_policy = typename PolicyHolder::preferred_integer_types_policy;
3401 using return_type =
3402 typename impl<FormatTraits>::template return_type<sign_policy, trailing_zero_policy,
3403 preferred_integer_types_policy>;
3404
3405 template <class IntervalTypeProvider>
3406 WJR_INTRINSIC_INLINE WJR_SAFEBUFFERS WJR_CONSTEXPR20 return_type
3407 operator()(IntervalTypeProvider, signed_significand_bits<FormatTraits> s,
3408 typename FormatTraits::exponent_int exponent_bits) noexcept {
3409 constexpr auto tag = IntervalTypeProvider::tag;
3410
3411 if constexpr (tag == policy::decimal_to_binary_rounding::tag_t::to_nearest) {
3412 return impl<FormatTraits>::template compute_nearest<
3413 sign_policy, trailing_zero_policy, IntervalTypeProvider,
3414 binary_to_decimal_rounding_policy, cache_policy, preferred_integer_types_policy>(
3415 s, exponent_bits);
3416 } else if constexpr (tag ==
3417 policy::decimal_to_binary_rounding::tag_t::left_closed_directed) {
3418 return impl<FormatTraits>::template compute_left_closed_directed<
3419 sign_policy, trailing_zero_policy, cache_policy, preferred_integer_types_policy>(
3420 s, exponent_bits);
3421 } else {
3422 static_assert(tag == policy::decimal_to_binary_rounding::tag_t::right_closed_directed,
3423 "");
3424 return impl<FormatTraits>::template compute_right_closed_directed<
3425 sign_policy, trailing_zero_policy, cache_policy, preferred_integer_types_policy>(
3426 s, exponent_bits);
3427 }
3428 }
3429};
3430} // namespace detail

3433// The interface function.
3435
3436template <class FormatTraits, class ExponentBits, class... Policies>
3437WJR_INTRINSIC_INLINE
3438 WJR_SAFEBUFFERS WJR_CONSTEXPR20 detail::to_decimal_return_type<FormatTraits, Policies...>
3439 to_decimal_ex(signed_significand_bits<FormatTraits> s, ExponentBits exponent_bits,
3440 Policies...) noexcept {
3441 // Build policy holder type.
3442 using policy_holder = detail::to_decimal_policy_holder<Policies...>;
3443
3444 return policy_holder::delegate(s, detail::to_decimal_dispatcher<FormatTraits, policy_holder>{},
3445 s, exponent_bits);
3446}

3449 class FormatTraits = ieee754_binary_traits<typename ConversionTraits::format,
3450 typename ConversionTraits::carrier_uint>,
3451 class... Policies>
3452WJR_INTRINSIC_INLINE
3453 WJR_SAFEBUFFERS WJR_CONSTEXPR20 detail::to_decimal_return_type<FormatTraits, Policies...>
3454 to_decimal(Float x, Policies... policies) noexcept {
3455 auto const br = make_float_bits<Float, ConversionTraits, FormatTraits>(x);
3456 auto const exponent_bits = br.extract_exponent_bits();
3457 auto const s = br.remove_exponent_bits();
3458 WJR_ASSERT(br.is_finite() && br.is_nonzero());
3459
3460 return to_decimal_ex(s, exponent_bits, policies...);
3461}

3486extern char *to_chars(CarrierUInt significand, int exponent, char *buffer) noexcept;
3487
3488template <size_t max_digits, class UInt>
3489constexpr char *print_integer_naive(UInt n, char *buffer) noexcept {
3490 char temp[max_digits]{};
3491 auto ptr = temp + sizeof(temp) - 1;
3492 do {
3493 *ptr = char('0' + n % 10);
3494 n /= 10;
3495 --ptr;
3496 } while (n != 0);
3497 while (++ptr != temp + sizeof(temp)) {
3498 *buffer = *ptr;
3499 ++buffer;
3500 }
3501 return buffer;
3502}
3503
3504template <class FloatFormat, class CarrierUInt>
3505constexpr char *to_chars_naive(CarrierUInt significand, int exponent, char *buffer) noexcept {
3506 // Print significand.
3507 {
3508 auto *const ptr =
3509 print_integer_naive<FloatFormat::decimal_significand_digits>(significand, buffer);
3510
3511 // Insert decimal dot.
3512 if (ptr > buffer + 1) {
3513 auto next = *++buffer;
3514 ++exponent;
3515 *buffer = '.';
3516 while (++buffer != ptr) {
3517 auto const temp = *buffer;
3518 *buffer = next;
3519 next = temp;
3520 ++exponent;
3521 }
3522 *buffer = next;
3523 }
3524 ++buffer;
3525 }
3526
3527 // Print exponent.
3528 *buffer = 'E';
3529 ++buffer;
3530 if (exponent < 0) {
3531 *buffer = '-';
3532 ++buffer;
3533 exponent = -exponent;
3534 }
3535 return print_integer_naive<FloatFormat::decimal_exponent_digits>(unsigned(exponent), buffer);
3536}
3537} // namespace detail

3588// Avoid needless ABI overhead incurred by tag dispatch.
3589template <class DecimalToBinaryRoundingPolicy, class BinaryToDecimalRoundingPolicy,
3590 class CachePolicy, class PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy, class DigitGenerationPolicy,
3591 class FormatTraits>
3592WJR_CONSTEXPR20 char *to_chars_n_impl(float_bits<FormatTraits> br, char *buffer) noexcept {
3593 auto const exponent_bits = br.extract_exponent_bits();
3594 auto const s = br.remove_exponent_bits();
3595
3596 if (br.is_finite(exponent_bits)) {
3597 if (s.is_negative()) {
3598 *buffer = '-';
3599 ++buffer;
3600 }
3601 if (br.is_nonzero()) {
3602 if (is_constant_evaluated()) {
3603 return policy::digit_generation::compact_t::to_chars<
3604 DecimalToBinaryRoundingPolicy, BinaryToDecimalRoundingPolicy, CachePolicy,
3605 PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>(s, exponent_bits, buffer);
3606 }
3607
3608 return DigitGenerationPolicy::template to_chars<
3609 DecimalToBinaryRoundingPolicy, BinaryToDecimalRoundingPolicy, CachePolicy,
3610 PreferredIntegerTypesPolicy>(s, exponent_bits, buffer);
3611 } else {
3612 buffer[0] = '0';
3613 buffer[1] = 'E';
3614 buffer[2] = '0';
3615 return buffer + 3;
3616 }
3617 } else {
3618 if (s.has_all_zero_significand_bits()) {
3619 if (s.is_negative()) {
3620 *buffer = '-';
3621 ++buffer;
3622 }
3623 // MSVC generates two mov's for the below, so we guard it inside
3624 // JKJ_IF_CONSTEVAL.
3625 if (is_constant_evaluated()) {
3626 buffer[0] = 'I';
3627 buffer[1] = 'n';
3628 buffer[2] = 'f';
3629 buffer[3] = 'i';
3630 buffer[4] = 'n';
3631 buffer[5] = 'i';
3632 buffer[6] = 't';
3633 buffer[7] = 'y';
3634 } else {
3635 builtin_memcpy(buffer, "Infinity", 8);
3636 }
3637 return buffer + 8;
3638 } else {
3639 buffer[0] = 'N';
3640 buffer[1] = 'a';
3641 buffer[2] = 'N';
3642 return buffer + 3;
3643 }
3644 }
3645}
